definitions.definition: the part in the middle of the arm where it bends, or the part of a piece of clothing that covers this area:
examples: Her arm was bandaged from the elbow to the fingers.

definitions.definition: to push someone rudely with your elbows so that you can move or have more space:
examples: He elbowed his way to the front of the crowd.

definitions.definition: to hit someone with your elbow, sometimes as a sign to make them notice or remember something:
examples: She elbowed me in the ribs before I could say anything.
